			<ns0:name>cbiffle@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/cbiffle@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Portions of the x86 validator require a TRUSTED_BUT_NOT_TCB definition to compile.  This is to ensure that, while the code is indeed trusted, it should not be accidentally linked into the sel_ldr.  This allows us to make certain shortcuts: for example, the code should be correct for expected inputs, but may not need to be hardened against malicious inputs.

However, the name is misleading: the code *is* TCB.  This bug is a reminder to future-me to rename this macro.  Something like TRUSTED_OFFLINE or TRUSTED_BUT_NOT_SEL_LDR or something.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-02-22T22:58:55.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-10-21T17:19:11.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>WontFix</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
